---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="David Weidman">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Profile Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 sm:gap-8 items-start mb-10">
      <img
        src="/images/profile.jpg"
        alt="David Weidman"
        class="w-40 h-40 sm:w-48 sm:h-48 object-contain rounded bg-white"
      />
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h1 class="mb-2">David Weidman</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
          AI Security Founder • Policy & Engineering<br />
          Master in Public Policy, Harvard Kennedy School
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
          <a
            href="https://senteguard.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded border border-gray-200 hover:border-gray-300"
          >
            SenTeGuard
          </a>
          <a
            href="/blog"
            class="text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded border border-gray-200 hover:border-gray-300"
          >
            Blog
          </a>
          <a
            href="/speaking"
            class="text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded border border-gray-200 hover:border-gray-300"
          >
            Speaking
          </a>
          <a
            href="/projects"
            class="text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded border border-gray-200 hover:border-gray-300"
          >
            Projects
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
          <p>
            <a href="mailto:David@senteguard.com">David@senteguard.com</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            <a href="mailto:DWeidman@hks.harvard.edu">DWeidman@hks.harvard.edu</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/david-weidman" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
              >LinkedIn</a
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Value Proposition -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <div class="rounded border border-gray-200 p-5 bg-white">
        <h2 class="mb-2">What I work on</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          I build security products and policy frameworks for the “meaning layer” of AI systems: preventing
          sensitive knowledge from leaking when employees summarize, paraphrase, translate, or repackage
          internal information through LLM tools.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-3">
          My focus is practical: enterprise AI adoption that holds up under real compliance constraints
          (privacy, export controls, regulated R&amp;D, and national-security environments), without slowing
          teams to a crawl.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Bio -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">About</h2>
      <div class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>
          I’m an AI security founder and policy-oriented engineer focused on “cognitive security”: how
          meaning moves through humans, models, and workflows, and how organizations can enforce boundaries
          when language models make it easy to transform and transmit knowledge.
        </p>

        <p>
          I graduated from the United States Military Academy at West Point (’16) with dual degrees in
          Computer Science and Mathematical Sciences. Early on, I built machine-learning systems for
          strategy games and worked on applied ML research in communications systems.
        </p>

        <p>
          In the U.S. Army, I served in operational and technical roles, including leading teams in
          cyber-relevant missions and advising senior commanders. That experience shaped how I think about
          real-world constraints: uncertainty, adversaries, and the need for systems that work under
          pressure.
        </p>

        <p>
          I’m currently completing an MPP at Harvard Kennedy School (International &amp; Global Affairs).
          In parallel,
          I’m building <a href="https://senteguard.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SenTeGuard</a>,
          a company whose mission is to protecting organzations' most sensitive ideas.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Current Focus -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">Current focus</h2>
    
      <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-3">
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">SenTeGuard:</span>
          A security layer for enterprise GenAI that detects, warns, flags and blocks risky content flows at the point of use,
          especially semantic leakage when employees summarize, paraphrase, translate, or abstract sensitive material.
        </li>
    
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Moyo:</span>
          An “information-space mapper” that crawls and maps an organization’s public-facing knowledge surface,
          then measures how close internal concepts are to becoming externally reachable through LLMs, search, and
          retrieval tools. I use it for outside-in risk discovery and targeted AI red-teaming that feeds directly into
          concrete controls and SenTeGuard deployments.
        </li>
    
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Joseki: WrapperHub:</span>
          A prompt-spec marketplace and version-control layer for reusable AI workflows. The goal is to make
          prompts and agentic “recipes” auditable, testable, and governable: with changelogs, licensing, security scoring,
          and organization-level guardrails for how prompts are shared and reused.
        </li>
    
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Cognitive Security Standards (CSS):</span>
          A governance and controls framework for meaning-based security and “boundary maintenance,” designed to align with
          enterprise compliance constraints and export-controlled technical data regimes.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <!-- Research interests -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">Research interests</h2>
      <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>AI security: semantic leakage, prompt injection, and inference risks</li>
        <li>Enterprise “cognitive firewalls” and boundary maintenance for LLM applications</li>
        <li>Governance and compliance for GenAI deployment in regulated environments</li>
        <li>National security and cyberwarfare policy in the LLM era</li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Three Papers In-Progress</span>
        </li>
        <li>   (1) The G&ouml;delian Limits of LLM-Reachable Intelligence (link)</li>
        <li>   (2) The Limits of Quantized Language: discrete vs. continuous idea space (link)</li>
        <li>   (3) Idea / Prompt Compressibility and Shareability (link)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Skills -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">Skills</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm mb-2">Technical</h3>
          <ul class="text-gray-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>Security engineering for GenAI systems (DLP, content risk, guardrails)</li>
            <li>Applied ML / LLM evaluation, red-teaming, and safety testing</li>
            <li>Backend systems, enterprise integrations, and deployment design</li>
            <li>Product strategy for B2B security and compliance tooling</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-sm mb-2">Policy &amp; leadership</h3>
          <ul class="text-gray-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>AI governance, national security, and risk frameworks</li>
            <li>Cross-functional leadership: technical teams and senior stakeholders</li>
            <li>Writing and briefing for technical + non-technical audiences</li>
            <li>International experience across defense and security contexts</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Languages -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">Languages</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
        In decreasing competence: English, Korean, French, Japanese, Italian, Mandarin
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">Contact</h2>
      <div class="text-gray-700 text-sm space-y-2">
        <p>
          <span class="font-semibold">Email:</span>
          <a href="mailto:DWeidman@hks.harvard.edu">Edu Email • </a>
          <a href="mailto:David@senteguard.com">SenTeGuard Email</a>
        </p>
        <p>
          <span class="font-semibold">LinkedIn:</span>
          <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/david-weidman" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
            > Personal • </a
          >
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/senteguard" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
            >SenTeGuard</a
          >
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Based in Cambridge, MA / Tokyo, JP • Open to speaking, advising, and enterprise pilots.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
